This is long so here are the points in summary:

 - Witchcraft and killer checks are meaningless

- It is equally likely that I am a wolf pulling 1 in 3 of my cards as HOUND over 3 checks as it is for HOUND to appear in anyone village player's check from the random pool, which is also 1 in 3.

-  It is actually much less likely that the two DOVE cards I have drawn in my checks BOTH came from the random pool - if one of them ever comes from my own pool, I am categorically not a wolf.

- None of this matters, it's still a 50/50 which card is mine. You don't care about how likely cards are to be drawn randomly - they can always be drawn. Even if unbeknownst to you there was a 100% chance of the random card being HOUND, you still wouldn't know which card is mine or not. That is why it's absolute nonsense to say otherwise.

Anyway, if you need more detail, here's 1,500 words...

# Tarot Card Checks #

### Jules 
- Magician/Magician


### Wolf 
- Magician/Death

### Butch

- Death/Magician
- Dove/Magician 
- Dove/Hound

# What does this mean?

It is very difficult to get any kind of intel from individual tarot card checks - as an item they rely on being used alongside other intel, or by having lots of tarot checks on the same person. In this case we have 5 total tarot uses in the game, 3 of them on me.

The main issue with a tarot check is there is often no way to distinguish which card belongs to the checked player and which is random from the pool, except in circumstances where two cards are the same or there is some other intel which confirms a player will have a certain card.

# The checks on me

If we assume I am appearing as WC because that has been checked by a rune, then my cards will be: DOVE (alignment) DEATH (I can kill, because of my items), MAGICIAN (I use witchcraft). 

So in 2 of 3 tarot cards Dove comes up, from my alignment - this CANNOT be one of my cards if I'm a wolf.

In 2 of 3 tarot cards we have a confirmation of the Magician check - this could either be from being a seer, being a SS or holding a rune.

In 1 of 3 tarot cards we have a death - this is expected from my pool as i have 2 items which give death cards.

In 1 of 3 tarot cards we have a hound. If I am a wolf, there would be a 1 in 3 chance that on every tarot check, this card is drawn - and on the surface it appears to be 3 checks on me, with 1 of them being a hound. Conclusive, right? 

No and I'll tell you why.

# Affirming the consequent

There is a logical fallacy which is being used to some extent here called affirming the consequent. It is not the only fallacy being used but it is part of what people are getting wrong, so it's useful to mention. An example of this itype of fallacy is:

- "The Shapeshifter has Magician cards"
- "Butch has a Magician card"
- "Therefore Butch is a Shapeshifter"

In this case, there are multiple reasons why someone has a Magician card, and so we can't infer from having magician cards which it is. The same is true of Death cards - because items cause you to look like you have Death. We can therefore discount all other cards except DOVE and HOUND, since a Shapeshifter cannot have DOVE and a Seer cannot have HOUND.

# Why the hound card cannot be used on its own

The above logic doesn't apply to this case because in this game there are no other ways a hound card could be from anything but a Shapeshifter (or werewolf after the direwolf has converted back). But the key thing here is we don't know whether I have a hound card or not. There are two cards presented: DOVE - which makes me legit and HOUND which makes me evil. Either of these cards can be drawn from me and either can be drawn from the random pool.

# But it's less likely a wolf card is drawn from the random pool?

Correct it is, on a single draw with the number players alive at the time of the check there were 15 possible cards from other players, only one of which would be a HOUND. So when drawing the random card, per check it would be 1 in 15 that the random card was a hound. This is not the full picture however, as Pumpkin would like you to think. 

The reality is that actually there have been 5 tarot card draws - with draws of 16/17, 14/15, 14/15, 11/12 and 11/12 for cards that are NOT hound. This makes it 67% chance of only drawing cards that are NOT hound on the random pool, assuming the hound card is in that pool. Therefore from all of the Tarot card checks in the game there is a 33% chance - 1 in 3 - that one HOUND card is drawn in the random check, assuming in each case the hound card is in that random pool.

So we have if I am a wolf, 1 in 3 that a HOUND card gets drawn each time from MY cards - we have had 3 checks and 1 in 3 has indeed been drawn, but equally we have a 1 in 3 chance that a hound card is drawn from ALL tarot checks - which we also have seen. 

The argument from Pumpkin has been that it's more likely I'm a wolf because they claim that it's "1 in 15" that that hound card came up for me - ignoring that I've been checked twice by them, three times in total AND ignoring the TOTAL chance of a hound card being drawn from the random pool, makes it 1 in 3 chance that we would see a hound card randomly drawn out of 5 checks.

So that chance they have been making out to be really unlikely, is not that unlikely actually. Even if you only count the checks on me that still close to 1 in 4 chance of drawing that random hound card out of the pool.

# But wait, what about DOVE cards?

DOVE is more complicated because it can refer to the alignment OR killing status of a player - but in this game every player that has claimed items has claimed killing items. So the last 4 tarot checks have only alignment doves, not killer doves - which wolves do not have. And I have drawn TWO dove cards in my tarot checks. The chances of me drawing both of those from the random pool is 7%.

Even if assume the worst and I am a wolf and Marvin didn't have a killing item thats still only a 13% chance of that random card drawing DOVE twice - making it MORE LIKELY it came from MY pool which cannot happen if I'm a wolf.

# Why this doesn't even matter
So this doesn't matter because regardless of how it was drawn, those are the cards that are drawn. I am either a Shapeshifter or I am a Seer. Those are the two options. Alternatively I either have the Hound card in my pool, or I do not. You do not know these things. This is what you are trying to determine.

There is a hound card drawn - does that card belong to me or was it from the pool? It's 50/50 which card is mine when you don't know if I'm a wolf or not. Nothing else matters because even if it's 1 in a million that a HOUND card is drawn from the random pool. it's still 50/50 whether that is MY card or not. All you care about is if that hound card belongs to me and no matter how you look at it, without knowing any more information about me - it's 50/50.

You know this because you can imagine a thought experiment where the second card is always hound, no matter what. If you didn't know this and you are asked if the hound card is mine or not, you have exactly the same decision to make - it's either my card or it's not.

It is 50/50 from your point of view because you do not know if I'm wolf or village. Nothing else matters in this decision about whether to lynch me - so it is totally irrelevant HOW the second card was picked. It was picked - now which one belongs to me?

Another way of looking at it is that I also drew DOVE twice from my checks - but from your point of view both of those could have been from the random pool, and it's 50/50 every time which card is mine. 

Separate out WHAT the card is from WHO it belongs to because what you are voting on is WHO it belongs to, and that choice is equal - so you're flipping a coin and you'd need to look at other information.

# Other reasons I'm probably not evil from your POV

If I'm evil - who is my teammate? Marsellus wanted me dead yesterday, I wanted to lynch Marvin - regardless of what anyone else wanted to do - and Wolf, Pumpkin and HoneyBunny all want me dead today. Where is my second wolf and why do they all want me dead?
